tasks.description:
In scripts/orchestrate-agents-v2.ts, inside the assessTaskComplexity() function (around line 1292), add a stateful pattern check AFTER the sovereign-mode early return and BEFORE the task_target override block. If the task description or ID contains stateful keywords AND test keywords, force routing to provider='anthropic', model='claude-sonnet-4-20250514', with routingReason='stateful pattern detected — cloud-exec override'. Log a [STATEFUL] warning to the console.

Stateful keywords to detect (case-insensitive, check task.description + task.id):
- 'circuit-breaker'
- 'state-machine'
- 'retry-logic'
- 'rate-limiter'
- 'connection-pool'
- 'stateful'

Test keywords (at least one must also be present):
- 'test'
- 'spec'
- 'verif'

Add a constant at the top of the function:
const STATEFUL_KEYWORDS = ['circuit-breaker', 'state-machine', 'retry-logic', 'rate-limiter', 'connection-pool', 'stateful'];
const TEST_KEYWORDS = ['test', 'spec', 'verif'];

Logic:
const taskText = `${task.id} ${task.description}`.toLowerCase();
const isStateful = STATEFUL_KEYWORDS.some(kw => taskText.includes(kw));
const isTest = TEST_KEYWORDS.some(kw => taskText.includes(kw));
if (isStateful && isTest) {
  log(c.yellow, `  [STATEFUL] Pattern detected in ${task.id} — routing to Claude Sonnet`);
  return { provider: 'anthropic', model: 'claude-sonnet-4-20250514', routingReason: 'stateful pattern detected — cloud-exec override' };
}

Only modify the assessTaskComplexity() function. Do not touch anything else.

In scripts/orchestrate-agents-v2.ts, make two targeted edits:

1. Line 2260: Change `const MAX_RETRIES = 10;` to `const MAX_RETRIES = 5;`

2. Around lines 2483-2485 (the final failure block after the retry loop), change the rejection block from:
  task.status = 'rejected';
  log(c.red, `\n✗ Task ${task.id} FAILED after ${MAX_RETRIES} attempts`);
  taskRun.status = 'rejected';

To:
  task.status = 'suspended';
  log(c.red, `\n⏸ Task ${task.id} SUSPENDED after ${MAX_RETRIES} attempts — queued for CEO review`);
  taskRun.status = 'suspended';
  taskRun.rejection_reason = `Auto-suspended: ${MAX_RETRIES} consecutive failures. Last rejection: ${lastReview?.summary || 'unknown'}`;

Also add 'suspended' to the SprintTask status union type at line 54:
Change: status: 'pending' | 'in_progress' | 'review' | 'approved' | 'rejected' | 'done' | 'skipped';
To: status: 'pending' | 'in_progress' | 'review' | 'approved' | 'rejected' | 'done' | 'skipped' | 'suspended';

Only make these three surgical edits. Do not touch anything else.
